		<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF INNERFLAME</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Monk</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;56</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;12 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;30 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;26 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline all hits landed by the monk will be for at least four times the base weapons/hand damage. For example: If you used a weapon with a base damage of 8, then you would receive a bonus of 32 damage on every hit for the duration of the discipline.  This discipline lasts for 12 seconds and has a base reuse time of 30 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the monk gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>YOU GUYS ARE CONFUSED</span><b>, By Smagh</b><br><br>In the description it says that it does 4 times the damage of your weapon/hand ADDED on to your normal hits. The reason they word it like that is because they want you to know the formula they use just so you are in the know. Most damages at higher levels do 4 the damage of the damage it says on the weapons. This discipline does an additional 4 times added on just like the first 4 is added on. For example with 12 damage weapons you usually do about 50 damage without this discipline, with this it'd add an additional 4 times the damage of the weapon's damage stats so an additional 50 damage. In other words it's usually going to double each hit you do. This is still remarkable but it's not quite 4 times your normal damage like you guys were saying.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>EXAMPLE</span><b>, By Zerric</b><br><br>Ok I use a Runed fighters staff ( 19 / 20 ).I can hit unbuffed for 93 dmg. Max
With this weapon and using the 56th level disc my dmg would look like this. Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric hits Mobx for 93 +(4 x 19) = 169,Zerric Kicks Mobx for 110 +(4 x 25) = 210.<P>
Therefore it does 4 times the BASE DMG of the weap. In my case 19. 19 x 4 = 76.. add this to my 93. Boom. 169



<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IT WOULD SEEM...</span><b>, By Leslie tu`styx</b><br><br>From reading the description of this, it would seem that it only adds 4 * (base_of_weapon) to your natural hit.
Someone already stated this further down the list, and I have to agree.  From the wording in the description, this does not increase your base damage by 4 rather adds 4x the base damage to your actual hit!
Sure it would be insane to have a 4x multiplier in addition to your current base multiplier, but realistically, that would make you near invincible for 9 seconds and you would just lay waste to any mob in front of you.  It would severly unbalance the game, and couldn't/wouldn't ever be a reality. This seems to be an excellent discipline and I look forward to attaining it.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>OF TRIBUNAL</span><b>, By Rimidal</b><br><br>All weapons have a damage multiplier depending on your weapon skill and offense skill. So a weapon with 8dmg, does not hit for 8damage, it hits for around 30.
Fists are 14/28, meaning they hit for around 40-60 each round. I assume that the four times base damage multiplier would make the fists 56/28. You would hit for around 200 a punch.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>MISCONCEPTIONS</span><b>, By Inno</b><br><br>This discipline adds 4 x BASE damge (the damage written in the DMG: section of the weapon when you click on it) to every blow. <P>

It will not add 200 as one person is saying.  The base damage on monks fists is 14, so it will add 56 to every punch we LAND during that period that the dicipline lasts.   For example,  if you are carrying a stave of Shielding (17/28) and a Whitened treant fist (14/28) then you will have 68 added to damage done by every blow landed on your primary hand, and 56 added to every blow from your off hand.  FYI Base damage on our kick is about 25, so it will add 100 to every kick we land in that period. <P>

The damage is additive and is dependent on the BASE damge on the weapon you are carrying.  With a haste buff a monk will RIP TO SHREDS any mob dumb enough to stand in this path while this discipline is in effect. 



<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
